{"parentUuid":"3c67d26c-7795-4739-ae23-77c7da4f4f2e","isSidechain":true,"userType":"external","cwd":"/home/ryan/formal-conjectures","sessionId":"e75cd3e8-170f-452c-b586-9cbe88f736e4","version":"2.1.71","gitBranch":"ai-erdos-7","agentId":"a24d785022acc6319","slug":"lucky-swimming-haven","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01Q3RDEAHpHCnkzwkSoSBuew","type":"tool_result","content":"     1→/-\n     2→Copyright 2026 The Formal Conjectures Authors.\n     3→\n     4→Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n     5→you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n     6→You may obtain a copy of the License at\n     7→\n     8→    https://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n     9→\n    10→Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n    11→distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n    12→WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n    13→See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n    14→limitations under the License.\n    15→-/\n    16→\n    17→import FormalConjectures.Util.ProblemImports\n    18→\n    19→/-!\n    20→# Erdős Problem 638\n    21→\n    22→Is it true that for every infinite cardinal $\\kappa$ there is a graph $G$ such that every\n    23→finite induced subgraph of $G$ belongs to a given family $S$ with the Ramsey property, and\n    24→every $\\kappa$-colouring of the edges of $G$ contains a monochromatic triangle?\n    25→\n    26→*Reference:* [erdosproblems.com/638](https://www.erdosproblems.com/638)\n    27→-/\n    28→\n    29→open SimpleGraph Cardinal\n    30→\n    31→namespace Erdos638\n    32→\n    33→/-- A symmetric colouring of a simple graph has a **monochromatic triangle**\n    34→    if three pairwise-adjacent vertices have all three edges the same colour. -/\n    35→def HasMonoTriangle {V : Type*} (G : SimpleGraph V) {α : Type*}\n    36→    (c : V → V → α) : Prop :=\n    37→  ∃ a b d : V, G.Adj a b ∧ G.Adj b d ∧ G.Adj a d ∧\n    38→    c a b = c b d ∧ c a b = c a d\n    39→\n    40→/-- The induced subgraph of $G$ pulled back along an embedding\n    41→    $f : \\operatorname{Fin} m \\hookrightarrow V$. -/\n    42→def inducedFinSubgraph {V : Type*} (G : SimpleGraph V) {m : ℕ}\n    43→    (f : Fin m ↪ V) : SimpleGraph (Fin m) where\n    44→  Adj i j := G.Adj (f i) (f j)\n    45→  symm _ _ h := G.symm h\n    46→  loopless i h := G.loopless (f i) h\n    47→\n    48→/-- Two graphs on $\\operatorname{Fin} m$ are isomorphic via a permutation of vertices. -/\n    49→def FinGraphIso {m : ℕ} (G H : SimpleGraph (Fin m)) : Prop :=\n    50→  ∃ σ : Equiv.Perm (Fin m), ∀ i j, G.Adj i j ↔ H.Adj (σ i) (σ j)\n    51→\n    52→/--\n    53→**Erdős Problem 638**\n    54→\n    55→Let $S$ be a family of finite graphs (indexed by vertex count) with the Ramsey\n    56→property: for every $n \\geq 1$, some member of $S$ forces a monochromatic triangle\n    57→under any $n$-colouring of its edges.\n    58→\n    59→Is it true that for every infinite cardinal $\\kappa$, there exists a graph $G$ such that\n    60→every finite induced subgraph of $G$ belongs (up to isomorphism) to $S$, and\n    61→every $\\kappa$-colouring of the edges of $G$ contains a monochromatic triangle?\n    62→-/\n    63→@[category research open, AMS 5]\n    64→theorem erdos_638 : answer(sorry) ↔\n    65→    ∀ (S : (m : ℕ) → Set (SimpleGraph (Fin m)))\n    66→      (_ : ∀ n : ℕ, n ≥ 1 →\n    67→        ∃ m : ℕ, ∃ G ∈ S m,\n    68→          ∀ (c : Fin m → Fin m → Fin n), (∀ u v, c u v = c v u) →\n    69→            HasMonoTriangle G c)\n    70→      (κ : Cardinal) (_ : ℵ₀ ≤ κ),\n    71→    ∃ (V : Type) (G : SimpleGraph V),\n    72→      (∀ (m : ℕ) (f : Fin m ↪ V),\n    73→        ∃ H ∈ S m, FinGraphIso (inducedFinSubgraph G f) H) ∧\n    74→      ∀ (α : Type) (_ : #α = κ) (c : V → V → α),\n    75→        (∀ u v, c u v = c v u) → HasMonoTriangle G c := by\n    76→  sorry\n    77→\n    78→end Erdos638\n    79→"}]},"uuid":"c8945b28-69b1-49b6-81d0-2c5d954b602b","timestamp":"2026-03-10T18:29:15.610Z","sourceToolAssistantUUID":"3c67d26c-7795-4739-ae23-77c7da4f4f2e"}
